TI  - Structural basis of CRISPR-Cas9 off-target activity.
PG  - 913-920
LID - 10.1038/s41586-024-07508-y [doi]
AB  - CRISPR-Cas9 genome editing is widely used for research and therapeutic 
      applications, but off-target activity remains a critical safety concern. 
      Here we present cryo-electron microscopy structures of Cas9 bound to 
      mismatched guide RNA-DNA duplexes, revealing the structural mechanisms 
      underlying tolerance of mismatches at different positions. Our structures 
      show that mismatches distal to the PAM are accommodated through local 
      distortions, whereas PAM-proximal mismatches destabilise the R-loop and 
      prevent HNH domain repositioning. These findings provide a structural 
      framework for understanding Cas9 fidelity and guide rational engineering 
      of high-fidelity variants.
